# User wording does not shorten the ship bar

These phrases do **not** waive the wait gate (step 5) or thread closure (step 6) in `git-pr-workflow-default.mdc`:

- "Merge everything" / "batch merge" / "land the queue"
- "Just merge" / "urgency" / frustration tone
- "CI green" / "checks passed" while threads are missing or unsettled
- Skipping the ~10–15 min post–green-CI re-poll

**Only** an explicit written waiver for that specific PR waives bot closeout for that PR.

